item.title: London house extension zigzags like a row of houses
item.description:
London house extension zigzags like a row of houses

Bureau de Change Architects gave this north London house extension a pleated ceiling to create the illusion it has been squashed onto the rear of the brick terraced property (+ slideshow). Bureau de Change Architects, which was co-founded by Katerina Dionysopoulou and Billy Mavropoulos, positioned the extension in the sunken garden at the back of the house.
